places.name: Anse Lazio Beach
places.perex: Anse Lazio is a beach situated in the northwest of Praslin Island, Seychelles, considered by Lonely Planet to be the best beach on Praslin,…

places.name: Victoria Clock Tower
places.perex: Also known as Lorloz, this national monument has been the most prominent feature of the small capital of Seychelles for over a century!

places.name: Beau Vallon
places.perex: Beau Vallon ist einer der 25 Verwaltungsbezirke der Seychellen. Mit nur 3,7 Quadratkilometern und 4049 Einwohnern ist er einer der dicht…

places.name: Vallée de Mai
places.perex: Das Vallée de Mai ist ein Nationalpark auf der Insel Praslin und eine der berühmtesten Sehenswürdigkeiten der Seychellen.

places.name: National Botanical Gardens
places.perex: Come enjoy the fascinating botanical gardens situated on the outskirts of Victoria! Admire the stunning plants and the giant land tortoises.

places.name: Grand Anse Beach
places.perex: The Praslin island sure has some of the most astonishing beaches one can ever see, and this one belongs to them, no doubt!

places.name: Anse Intendance Beach
places.perex: Considered equal to the best beaches of the world, the fascinating beach should not be missed by any chance! A truly remarkable place!

places.name: Anse Royale Beach
places.perex: Yet another of the astonishing beaches of the Mahé Island, the one in Anse Royale is somewhat more remote and serene. Enjoy the paradise!

places.name: Cote d’Or Beach
places.perex: The fascinating beach offers an amazing place for everyone to have fun or just relax. It certainly belongs to the best Praslin has to offer!

places.perex: Der Nationalpark Sainte Anne Marine National Park wurde 1973 im Staatsgebiet der Seychellen, genauer dem Verwaltungsbezirk Mont Fleuri,…

places.name: Tea Factory
places.perex: One of the most famous and frequented tourist spots on the island. The factory provides an informative tour during which you can taste the…

places.name: Bird Island
places.perex: Bird Island ist die nördlichste Insel der Seychellen. Sie liegt rund 100 km von der Hauptinsel Mahé entfernt und wird zu den sogenannten…

places.name: Police Bay and Petit Police
places.perex: The southern point of the island is a popular destination for sunbathing or admiring the unspoilt nature. Swimming is way too dangerous here.

places.name: Aldabra
places.perex: Vorlage:Infobox Atoll/Wartung/HoeheFehltAldabra ist das größte Atoll des Indischen Ozeans.

places.name: Cousin
places.perex: Cousin zählt mit einer Gesamtgröße von etwa 27 Hektar zu den kleineren der 115 Seychellen-Inseln.

places.name: Anse aux Pins
places.perex: The beautiful coastal area offers a piece of paradise - the beaches have crystal clear water and the sand is pure. An amazing experience!

places.name: Desroches
places.perex: Die Insel Desroches liegt 230 km südwestlich von Mahé, der Hauptinsel der Seychellen, und gehört zur Gruppe der Amiranten.

places.name: Petite Anse
places.perex: The wonderful beach located on the southwestern part of of the Mahé island is simply breathtaking. Do make sure you stop by.

places.name: Giant Tortoise Farm
places.perex: The astonishing farm is just the perfect place to meet and learn something more about the fascinating giant turtles who inhabit the island!

places.name: Cosmoledo
places.perex: Vorlage:Infobox Atoll/Wartung/HoeheFehlt

places.name: Le Jardin Du Roi Spice Garden
places.perex: The fascinating garden grows a variety of spices and offers various meals in which these spices are used. Enjoy the meal with a scenic view!

places.name: Curieuse
places.perex: Curieuse ist eine Insel der Seychellen und wird wie alle Granitinseln zu den inneren Seychellen um die Hauptinsel Mahé gezählt.

places.name: Seychelles Natural History Museum
places.perex: The Seychelles Natural History Museum is a natural history museum in the Seychelles.

places.name: Frégate
places.perex: Frégate, gelegentlich auch Frigate genannt, ist eine Insel im Indischen Ozean und gehört zu den granitischen „Inner Islands“ der Seychellen.

places.name: Sir Selwyn Selwyn Clarke Market
places.perex: A busy and colourful market offers the very atmosphere of the Seychellois way of life. It is the beating heart of Victoria!

places.name: Eagle Nest
places.perex: The highest point of La Digue is the Nid d'Aigles with an altitude of 333 m. It offers spectacular views of the La Digue and Praslin islands.

places.name: La Pause
places.perex: The noble St. Paul's is both the Cathedral of the whole Diocese and the Anglican parish church of Victoria.

places.name: Platte
places.perex: Platte ist eine zur Republik der Seychellen gehörende Koralleninsel im Indischen Ozean.

places.name: Frégate Island Airport
places.perex: Frégate Island Airport is an airstrip serving Frégate Island in the Seychelles. The runway is along the northeast shore of the island.

places.name: Bird Island Airport
places.perex: Bird Island Airport serves Bird Island, a small island 100 kilometres northwest of Victoria, the capital of the Seychelles.

places.name: Marie Louise Island Airport
places.perex: Marie Louise Island Airport is an airstrip serving Marie Louise Island in the Seychelles.

places.name: Denis Island
places.perex: Denis Island ist nach Bird Island die zweitnördlichste Insel der Republik der Seychellen.

places.name: National Youth Service
places.perex: The National Youth Service was a heavily criticized program implemented by the government of Seychelles.

places.name: DoubleTree Resort & Spa by Hilton Hotel Seychelles - Allamanda
Level 3 Bar
places.perex: Voted the best bar on the island, it sure does attract a diverse crowd - especially on weekends. Do not miss out on this experience.

places.name: Lémuria Resort Golf Course
places.perex: An amazing golf course with a variety of challenging holes to enjoy! Come play the game of the gentlemen on the island of Praslin!

places.name: Praslin Museum
places.perex: Situated on Cote D’Or, the first museum on the island showcases the traditions and culture of Seychelles and also features a stunning…

places.name: Pirates Arms Pub
places.perex: A popular and rather inexpensive restaurant serving cold beverages and tasty meals. Do stop by if you like pirates for this place is fun!

places.name: Lémuria Resort Boutiques
places.perex: The fascinating resort is a great tourist destination to visit: there are three boutiques, a golf course, and much more.

places.name: Domaine de Val des Pres (Craft Village)
Le Reef Golf Club
places.perex: Come play and enjoy the game of the gentlemen! Despite the course being a small one, the game is still fun, and the surroundings are great!

places.name: Black Pearl
places.perex: Three attractions in one: a giant clam farm, pearl farm and a store. Learn about clams, how they eat and reproduce or buy some jewellery!

places.name: Kenwyn House
places.perex: The Kenwyn house is a gem of the French colonial architecture. It houses an art gallery and and an astonishing jewellery store.

places.name: Arul Mihu Navasakthi Vinayagar
places.perex: The only Hindu temple in the whole Seychelles was built in 1992. It was named after Lord Vinayagar: the god of safety and prosperity.

places.name: The Sanctuary at Roche Caiman
places.perex: Originally an artificial wetland site, it was transformed into a wildlife sanctuary in 1987. Today it houses a variety of fauna and flora.

places.name: Tom Bower's Sculptures Studio
places.perex: Tom Bowers is a highly original sculptor, whose art depicts the beauty and serenity of the island life. Come admire or buy his work!

places.name: Antik Colony
places.perex: The popular shop situated in the premises the Pirate Arms' Arcade is just the place to visit if you want to buy a true Seychellois souvenir!

places.name: Sunstroke Studio
places.perex: The studios situated near the marketplace showcase products which include unique hand painted silk pictures, pareos and scarves.

places.name: L'Union Estate
places.perex: An informal theme park: the former coconut plantation offers demonstration of way of life of the past. Also offers horse rides and tortoises.

places.name: Île Cocos Marine National Park
places.perex: The fascinating island that is often featured in promotional brochures offers a piece of paradise. It is reachable from Praslin and La Digue.

places.name: Veuve Reserve
places.perex: The fascinating reserve island is the very home of the rare Black Paradise Flycatcher - there are only about 200 in existence.

places.name: Barbara Jenson Studio
places.perex: The beach side studio is a workplace of Barbara, who is a fulltime painter living and working on the La Digue island. Do visit her gallery!

places.name: Seychelles National Archive
places.perex: The archive serves as the guardian of the country's records of the past. Situated in the National Library, it offers exhibits and more.

places.name: Aride Island Nature Reserve
places.perex: The marvelous nature reserve is an awesome habitat with numerous endemic bird specimen, rich natural vegetation and marine life.

places.name: Beach Bar Restaurant
places.perex: Situated at a hotel near the Cote D'Or beach, it serves great long cool drinks or cocktails to enjoy as well as light meals to taste.

places.name: "Zonm Lib" Liberation Monument
places.perex: The national monument represents a major political landmark from the Seychellois history: it is a powerful symbol of freedom and liberty.

places.name: Silhouette Marine National Park
places.perex: The island has managed to avoid the deforestation which sadly affected other islands. It was proclaimed a marine park on 26 October 1987.

places.name: Le Duc de Praslin Hotel Gift Store
places.perex: The gift store situated in the premises of one of the hotels located near the Anse Volbert beach offers a variety of interesting souvenirs.

places.name: Le Dauphin
places.perex: The restaurant situated in a hotel near near the Anse Volbert beach offers authentic and tasty traditional Creole cuisine to enjoy!

places.name: Casino des Îles
places.perex: The amazing casino is renowned for its focus on poker. It also offers a wide variety of slot machines for the visitors to enjoy.

places.name: Bicentennial Monument
places.perex: The three pairs of wings created by Lorenzo Appiani were erected in 1978 to commemorate the 200th anniversary of the city of Victoria.

places.name: Cathedral of Immaculate Conception
places.perex: The imposing Cathedral is one of the largest features of the Victoria city. It is an architectural gem worth stopping by.

places.name: Cap Samy Art Gallery
places.perex: A beautiful seaside gallery that displays and sells the works of Sheila Markham. Her sculptures and painting depict the life on the islands.

places.name: Ancient Anse Boudin police station & clinic
Michael Adams Studio
places.perex: Michael Adams has been living and working in Seychelles ever since 1972. Come see his vivid art in his amazing gallery!

places.name: Katiolo
places.perex: The open-air discotheque is considered the best on the archipelago by many. It has strict rules: no shorts or flip flops and adults-only!

places.name: Ozone
places.perex: A fierce competitor to Katiolo, the nightclub only opens on weekends and tries to attract customers with quality music, raffles and prizes.

places.name: New Emerald Cove Boutique
places.perex: A great boutique situated in the premises of a hotel situated at Anse La Farine beach. Worth stopping by if you are in the area.

places.name: Tequila Boom Nightclub
places.perex: The popular nightclub plays latest club music and is often visited at weekends, when it offers happy hours. Worth checking out!

places.name: La Domus
places.perex: Built in 1934 to house Swiss missionaries, the magnificent two-story monument containing an aquaduct is an oustanding architectural gem.

places.name: Granite Boulder
places.perex: Situated close to the Union Estate, the wonderful granite boulder will certainly catch your eye. A spectacular piece of natural sculpture!

places.name: The Jungle
places.perex: The renowned club is considered to be the flagship of weekend nightlife in Praslin by many. Dancers head to the club en masse!

places.name: National Museum of History
places.perex: A nice little museum summing up the history of Seychelles. Despite being interesting, most of the information is only available in French.

places.name: Azzura Pro-Dive
places.perex: The amazing company offers a variety of trips to enjoy. Come explore the fascinating diving spots in the crystal clear waters near La Digue!

places.name: Oxygen Nightclub
places.perex: The amazingly fun nightclub on the east coast of the Praslin Island is a must visit! It requires a smart casual dress code and the age of 18.

places.name: Plantation House
places.perex: The plantation house was constructed aroud 1861 as the home of family Dauban. It showcases a distinctive Creole architectural style.

places.name: Berjaya Resort Casino
places.perex: An amazing casino and a fun place to enjoy. Situated in a hotel at Beau Vallon, it is only a short ride away from the centre of Victoria!

places.name: Lovenut
places.perex: The popular nightclub situated in the northern part of Victoria is a must-visit if you are in for some serious partying!

places.name: Deepam Cinema
places.perex: The popular cinema literally has no competition, as it is the only cinema in the Seychelles!

places.name: Nigel Henri Studio
places.perex: The amazing local artist Nigel Henri focuses on original acrylic paintings on canvas. Come see or buy his amazing works!

places.name: Amusement Centre
places.perex: Easily the most frequented casino in Victoria, it offers around 200 loose slot machines. It requires formal dress code after 18:00.

places.name: Bel Air Cemetery
places.perex: The island's first official burial ground allegedly features a a giant that should be buried here. It may be an interesting visit!

places.name: Studio Gallery Baie Lazare
places.perex: Situated at the Valmer resort, the little gallery exhibits art by Gerard Devoud, whose works include painting of the Seychelles archipelago.

places.name: French Cultural Centre
places.perex: The center's library is open to anyone, not just members. It also has a great cafeteria and organizes various events for the evenings.

places.name: Dauban Mausoleum
places.perex: The mausoleum was built in a serene and secluded place amid lush vegetation. It is an imposing architectural gem that should be seen.

places.name: Sheikh Sultan Bin Khalifa Al Nahyan Masjid
Seychelles Fire and Rescue Services Agency
Sheikh Muhammad Bin Khalifa Al-Nahayan Mosque
